Node.Notes: Uncertain. Most switch the order and translate as two vocatives "O Yahweh, the God of vengeance." However, the word order may indicate a nominal clause instead "A God of vengeance [is] Yahweh" (LXX supports this interpretation of the syntax).

Apparently an example of stairstep parallelism--the verb "will be jubilant" is not supplied until the second half. Seems to function to catch readers' attention and move them to want to bring the thought to completion.
Either "[he is] the one teaching humans knowledge" or carry over "[does not] the one who teaches humans knowledge rebuke?"
